author: ABC Radio National
title: Monday Finance with Tony Boyd
text:
Monday 19 October 2015 6:54AM (view full episode) 
Westpac caught home owners and the markets by surprise last week, announcing a 20 basis point lift in its standard variable home loan rates. 
It's a decision that appears to already be playing on the minds of potential home owners, with the weekend seeing one of the lowest auction clearance rates in recent years. 
So, will the other banks follow suit? 
The Australian Financial Review 's Tony Boyd joins Fran Kelly on RN Breakfast to preview the week ahead in business and finance.
